    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Chop your<strong> basil </strong>finely, including the stalks and dice your <strong>tomato[es] </strong>as finely as you can</p><p>Add the <strong>diced tomato</strong> and <strong>chopped basil </strong>to a small bowl with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong>, season with a little <strong>salt</strong>, <strong>sugar</strong> and a crack of <strong>black pepper</strong> and give everything a good mix up, then set aside \u2013 these are your <strong>bruschetta tomatoes</strong></p><p><strong><span class=\"text-danger\">Tip: Cooking for kids? Slice tomato into rounds and leave plain!</span></strong></p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/king-prawn-and-courgette-risotto-with-bruschetta-tomatoes/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Peel and finely dice your <strong>brown onion[s]</strong></p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Grate your <strong>courgette[s]</strong></p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/king-prawn-and-courgette-risotto-with-bruschetta-tomatoes/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Dissolve your <strong>vegetable stock mix</strong> in 750ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[975ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[1.4L]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/king-prawn-and-courgette-risotto-with-bruschetta-tomatoes/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>chopped onion</strong>,<strong> chopped garlic </strong>and<strong> grated courgette</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 5-6 min or until beginning to soften and caramelise</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/king-prawn-and-courgette-risotto-with-bruschetta-tomatoes/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once everything has slightly softened, reduce the heat to medium</p><p>Add your <strong>arborio rice</strong> and cook for 1 min, stirring to coat the grains</p><p>Add the<strong> vegetable</strong> <strong>stock</strong> a ladle at a time, stirring continuously for 25-30 min or until all of the stock is absorbed and the rice is cooked</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/king-prawn-and-courgette-risotto-with-bruschetta-tomatoes/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>When the rice is almost cooked, drain your <strong>king prawns</strong>, then add them to the pan with your <strong>Chinese rice wine</strong></p><p>Cook for 4-5 min further or until the prawns are cooked through</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/king-prawn-and-courgette-risotto-with-bruschetta-tomatoes/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the prawns are cooked, stir through your <strong>grated Italian hard cheese</strong>, a small pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and a knob of <strong>butter</strong> \u2013 this is your <strong>king prawn & courgette risotto</strong></p><p><strong><span class=\"text-danger\">Tip: Cooking for kids? Save a little grated Italian hard cheese!</span></strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/king-prawn-and-courgette-risotto-with-bruschetta-tomatoes/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>king prawn & courgette risotto</strong> and top with the <strong>bruschetta tomatoes</strong></p><p><strong><span class=\"text-danger\">Tip: Cooking for kids? Serve the tomato rounds to the side</span></strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
